		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">MottZilla wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I could swear I saw a SNES game with a debug feature that included some kind of CPU usage meter.</div><br />There are probably several, but Final Fight has a debug mode with this CPU meter.<br /><br />Esposo: since CRT TVs draw the image from top-left to bottom-right in a zigzag (&quot;raster scan&quot;) fashion, a higher-up &quot;timing&quot; arrow or BG colour change means LESS CPU time used; and a colour change, etc. seen near the bottom of the screen means MORE CPU time is being used.

		

